	<div id="comment_top_64424246" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64424246" name="comment_link_64424246" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23302472&amp;cid=64424246" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64424246)" >Presumably</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64424246" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64424246); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81">necro81</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81">( 917438 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64424246">		
		on Thursday April 25, 2024 @11:38AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23302472&amp;cid=64424246">#64424246</a>)
		<small><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81/journal/" title="Wednesday March 07, 2007 @06:30PM" class="user_journal_display">Journal</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64424246">Because the number is across the entire EV unit, that $1.3bn loss probably accounts for design, tooling up factories, etc.  In other words, non-recurring expenses (NRE) before you build a single vehicle.  It feels a bit unfair to report that as a loss of $130k/vehicle.  It is not as though the bill of materials (all the components in the vehicle) or cost-of-goods-sold (BOM + labor + other per-device costs) is $130k over MSRP.  <br> <br>

Eventually, yes, you need to <i>make</i> money on each vehicle to eventually recoup the NRE, otherwise you don't have a business.  But the time horizon is quite different than a single quarter or fiscal year.<br> <br>

Someone somewhere probably has the info: by comparable measures, how deep in the red was Tesla when they were only a few 10k units into Model S production?</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64424246">
